<h2 id="relationships">Relationships</h2>
<p class="lead">Start your discussion by reviewing Pastor Craig‚Äôs key points.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.bible.com/bible/111/joh.13.34-35.niv">John 13:34-35</a></p>

<p>How technology is changing relationships:</p>

<ol>
  <li>The term <strong>friend</strong> is evolving.</li>
  <li>We‚Äôre becoming <strong>addicted</strong> to immediate affirmation.</li>
  <li>We have the power to do friendships on our own <strong>terms</strong>.</li>
</ol>

<p><a href="https://www.bible.com/bible/111/heb.10.24-25.niv">Hebrews 10:24-25</a></p>

<p>Let‚Äôs get practical:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Be <strong>present</strong>. <a href="https://www.bible.com/bible/111/rom.12.9-13.niv">Romans 12:9-10, and 13</a></li>
  <li>Be <strong>engaged</strong>. <a href="https://www.bible.com/bible/111/1pe.4.8.niv">1 Peter 4:8</a>, <a href="https://www.bible.com/bible/111/1jo.3.18.niv">1 John 3:18</a>, <a href="https://www.bible.com/bible/111/joh.13.34-35.niv">John 13:34-35</a></li>
</ol>

